'''''X-Wing: Wedge's Gamble''''' is the second installment in the [[Star Wars: X-Wing (novel series)|''X-Wing'']] series of novels, released in [[1996]]. It was written by [[Michael A. Stackpole]]. The audio version was narrated by [[Henry Thomas]].

==Publisher's summary==
''It is the evil heart of a battered and reeling Empire: Coruscant, the giant city-world from whose massive towers the Imperial High Command directs the war. The Rebels will invade this mighty citadel in a daring move to bring the Empire to its knees. But first Wedge Antilles and his X-wing pilots must infiltrate Coruscant to gain vital intelligence information. Capture means death, or worse&mdash;enslavement by the vicious leader known as "Iceheart," Ysanne Isard, now Emperor in all but name. And one of Rogue Squadron's own is already her slave, a traitor hidden behind a mask of innocence, working to betray both colleagues and the Rebellion itself.''

==Plot summary==
A [[Standard month/Legends|month]] after the conquest of [[Borleias/Legends|Borleias]], the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] and [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] have to deal with [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Probe droid/Legends|probes]] by the rogue [[Warlord/Legends|Warlord]] [[Zsinj]], the apparent [[Death/Legends|death]] of member [[Bror Jace]], and re-populating the [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] with new, hotshot members, [[Aril Nunb]] and [[Pash Cracken]]. With worries of attacks by Zsinj's forces, the [[Provisional Council of the Alliance of Free Planets|Provisional Council of the Alliance]], including [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Princess Leia Organa]] and [[Borsk Fey'lya]], meet and decide that an invasion of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] must proceed. With a decision that criminals from the [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]] organization, [[Prison/Legends|imprisoned]] on [[Kessel/Legends|Kessel]], could be released on Coruscant to help bring resistance against the Empire, the Rogues are first sent to Kessel. Then they free a number of criminals that [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran]] himself sent there, including [[Zekka Thyne]] and his girlfriend, [[Inyri Forge]], sister to former Rogue member [[Lujayne Forge|Lujayne]].

After the Black Sun members are placed on Coruscant, Rogue's members are covertly inserted onto the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] in small groups. Corran and [[Erisi Dlarit]] are put together and meet with [[Alliance Intelligence]] [[Agent/Legends|agent]] [[Winter Celchu|Winter]], [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge]] and Pash Cracken are together and meet with agent and Corran's former partner [[Iella Wessiri Antilles|Iella Wessiri]], and the rest of the Rogues are brought by [[Mirax Terrik Horn|Mirax Terrik]] to the [[Alien Protection Zone/Legends|Invisisec]], an underworld for many of the poor, [[Alien/Legends|non-Humans]] on Coruscant. After Mirax is compromised and meets with Wedge and Corran sees [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]] speaking to Imperial [[Agent/Legends|agent]] [[Kirtan Loor]], the Rogues think they may have a traitor in their midst. Meanwhile, the Imperial forces, led by [[Ysanne Isard]], are creating a virus that attacks non-Humans, the [[Krytos virus]], and are planning on giving the Rebels Coruscant when it is ready. They believe that the Rebels will be taxed for resources if they try to help everyone with the virus and will soon lose Coruscant once again and be finally defeated.

The Rogues are informed, after plans from [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar]] and Fey'lya are approved, that they must take down Coruscant's [[Planetary shield/Legends|planetary shields]] at a precise time in order for the Rebel attack to succeed. After some minor failures and the capture of Aril Nunb, the group formulates a plan. Told of the Rebels' impending invasion by a traitor in Rogue Squadron, Isard accelerates the plan to release the virus, informs Loor that he is to stay as a form of resistance when the Rebels invade, and readies herself for an escape from the planet. With help from Black Sun, a group of [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] [[Spy/Legends|spies]], and the rest of the Alliance Intelligence on the planet, the Rogues are able to take down the shields in time for the Rebel fleet to arrive. With only two [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyers]] sent to defend the planet, it easily falls into Rebel hands. However, Corran, investigating a fleeing [[Starship/Legends|ship]], crashes his [[Z-95 Headhunter/Legends|Z-95 Headhunter]] when an outside force takes control of it. Although Aril Nunb is found safe and the non-Humans of the Rogues are treated and cured of the virus, the squadron ends in turmoil with Corran's apparent death and the arrest of Tycho as the apparent traitor responsible for his death. The novel ends with Corran waking as a captive aboard a ship, where Isard informs him that he is on his way to the prison and [[Torture/Legends|torture]] facility ''[[Lusankya/Legends|Lusankya]]''.

